WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:18.852 --> 00:00:21.062 position:50% align:center
Thanks a lot
for helping out today.

00:00:21.104 --> 00:00:22.564 position:50% align:center
We better hurry
and get this stuff home

00:00:22.605 --> 00:00:24.733 position:50% align:center
before Sota decides
to eat the house.

00:00:24.774 --> 00:00:25.775 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:00:25.817 --> 00:00:27.360 position:50% align:center
Well, he is a growing boy.

00:00:27.402 --> 00:00:30.613 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:00:30.655 --> 00:00:41.291 position:50% align:center
[singing in Japanese]

00:00:41.332 --> 00:00:42.334 position:50% align:center
Anime fan?

00:00:42.375 --> 00:00:43.793 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
Hmm?!

00:00:43.835 --> 00:00:45.503 position:50% align:center
Wait. Was I singing?

00:00:45.545 --> 00:00:46.629 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA]
Mm-hmm.

00:00:46.671 --> 00:00:48.673 position:50% align:center
You've got a nice
set of pipes on ya, Hori.

00:00:48.715 --> 00:00:50.717 position:50% align:center
I definitely do not!

00:00:50.759 --> 00:00:53.595 position:50% align:center
I just sang an anime
theme song in public.

00:00:53.636 --> 00:00:55.180 position:50% align:center
I can't believe it.

00:00:55.221 --> 00:00:57.265 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA] What's wrong
with liking anime music?

00:00:57.307 --> 00:00:59.309 position:50% align:center
Nothing if that's
what you're into.

00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:01.144 position:50% align:center
It is not my thing though.

00:01:01.186 --> 00:01:02.604 position:50% align:center
But Sota's all about it,

00:01:02.645 --> 00:01:05.899 position:50% align:center
and he plays it so much
even I know the lyrics now.

00:01:05.940 --> 00:01:07.233 position:50% align:center
That's fair enough.

00:01:07.275 --> 00:01:09.194 position:50% align:center
So what music do you like?

00:01:09.235 --> 00:01:12.781 position:50% align:center
What I like? Let me think.

00:01:13.573 --> 00:01:15.492 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
I have no idea what's popular!

00:01:15.533 --> 00:01:18.411 position:50% align:center
But I know all the words
to a friggin' anime theme!

00:01:18.453 --> 00:01:19.788 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA]
Hmm.

00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:23.958 position:50% align:center
Hey, I'm home!

00:01:24.417 --> 00:01:25.210 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO]
Welcome back!

00:01:25.251 --> 00:01:27.504 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:01:27.545 --> 00:01:29.714 position:50% align:center
Hold up. Mom?

00:01:29.756 --> 00:01:31.549 position:50% align:center
Hi!

00:03:02.849 --> 00:03:05.560 position:50% align:center
Oh-ho. So I take it you've
been having lots of fun

00:03:05.602 --> 00:03:07.062 position:50% align:center
with this new friend.

00:03:07.103 --> 00:03:08.646 position:50% align:center
[SOTA]
Uh-huh! Sure have.

00:03:08.688 --> 00:03:11.149 position:50% align:center
He comes over all the
time to play with me!

00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:13.151 position:50% align:center
He even bought me
this neat book!

00:03:13.193 --> 00:03:15.779 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO]
Well that was nice of him!

00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:17.864 position:50% align:center
And nice of you
to bring him around!

00:03:17.906 --> 00:03:21.326 position:50% align:center
So what's he like? Is he cute?

00:03:21.368 --> 00:03:24.621 position:50% align:center
Actually, he kinda reminds me
of the dark and twisted villain

00:03:24.662 --> 00:03:27.082 position:50% align:center
you'd find in a detective movie.

00:03:29.376 --> 00:03:32.003 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO] Uh. That's a strange
description for someone

00:03:32.045 --> 00:03:34.381 position:50% align:center
who's friends with both you
and your younger brother.

00:03:34.422 --> 00:03:37.050 position:50% align:center
Strange, but true.

00:03:37.092 --> 00:03:40.303 position:50% align:center
Either way, I'd love to talk
with him one-on-one sometime!

00:03:40.345 --> 00:03:43.139 position:50% align:center
I see no logical reason
for that to happen!

00:03:43.181 --> 00:03:44.474 position:50% align:center
'Kay. All done.

00:03:44.516 --> 00:03:48.520 position:50% align:center
Ahh! Thank you, Kyoko!
That felt great!

00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:51.523 position:50% align:center
So, anyway.
This boy have a name?

00:03:51.564 --> 00:03:52.524 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:03:52.565 --> 00:03:55.151 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO]
Your dark villain.

00:03:55.193 --> 00:03:57.153 position:50% align:center
Oh. Yeah, his name's Miyamura.

00:03:57.195 --> 00:03:58.321 position:50% align:center
That's his last name?

00:03:58.363 --> 00:04:02.450 position:50% align:center
Yeah. His first name is... Uh...

00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:04.327 position:50% align:center
What is Miaymura's first name?

00:04:04.369 --> 00:04:05.995 position:50% align:center
I have no clue.

00:04:11.126 --> 00:04:12.502 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
This is insane.

00:04:12.544 --> 00:04:15.380 position:50% align:center
He's been coming over to
my house for forever and a day,

00:04:15.422 --> 00:04:19.050 position:50% align:center
and I never thought
to ask what his first name is!

00:04:19.092 --> 00:04:22.220 position:50% align:center
Why'd our teacher have to take
the attendance sheet with him?

00:04:25.682 --> 00:04:28.184 position:50% align:center
[HORI] No harm in outright
asking, is there?

00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:32.105 position:50% align:center
Hey! So, uh, Miyamura!

00:04:32.147 --> 00:04:33.690 position:50% align:center
You don't have
a first name, do you?

00:04:33.732 --> 00:04:35.275 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:04:35.316 --> 00:04:36.484 position:50% align:center
Nope! Not happening!

00:04:36.526 --> 00:04:38.778 position:50% align:center
That's the absolute last way
I should figure this out!

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:40.864 position:50% align:center
Let's go get changed for gym.

00:04:42.657 --> 00:04:44.993 position:50% align:center
[IURA] Miyamura. You know
what we're doing today?

00:04:45.035 --> 00:04:46.953 position:50% align:center
I think it's a combined class.

00:04:46.995 --> 00:04:48.580 position:50% align:center
--[HORI exhales]
--[IURA] Huh?

00:04:48.621 --> 00:04:51.082 position:50% align:center
[HORI] Somebody,
call him by his first name!

00:04:51.124 --> 00:04:52.208 position:50% align:center
C'mon, boys!

00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:53.293 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:04:53.335 --> 00:04:55.628 position:50% align:center
Hori's been watching us
get undressed!

00:04:55.670 --> 00:04:57.130 position:50% align:center
What's with her?

00:04:57.172 --> 00:04:58.048 position:50% align:center
For real?

00:04:58.089 --> 00:04:59.424 position:50% align:center
Why would you peep on them?

00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:01.051 position:50% align:center
You frustrated or what?

00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:02.302 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:05:02.344 --> 00:05:04.471 position:50% align:center
[shrieks]

00:05:12.979 --> 00:05:14.898 position:50% align:center
Damn it all.

00:05:14.939 --> 00:05:18.193 position:50% align:center
If he were a little
bit smarter, I'd know!

00:05:18.234 --> 00:05:19.944 position:50% align:center
[ISHIKAWA]
Yo. You heading home?

00:05:19.986 --> 00:05:22.655 position:50% align:center
Hey, Toru! Your timing
couldn't be better!

00:05:22.697 --> 00:05:23.698 position:50% align:center
It's about Miyamura.

00:05:23.740 --> 00:05:24.699 position:50% align:center
I was wondering if you--

00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:26.743 position:50% align:center
Are you serious?

00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:29.120 position:50% align:center
My heart's still in
the process of healing.

00:05:29.162 --> 00:05:30.955 position:50% align:center
Give me time.

00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:35.919 position:50% align:center
Wait! Some help you are!

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:38.088 position:50% align:center
Who knew trying to find out
a person's first name

00:05:38.129 --> 00:05:40.215 position:50% align:center
would be so exhausting.

00:05:40.256 --> 00:05:42.133 position:50% align:center
Kyoko, what's wrong, huh?

00:05:42.175 --> 00:05:44.844 position:50% align:center
I hope the curry's not putting
that sour look on your face.

00:05:44.886 --> 00:05:47.263 position:50% align:center
[HORI] We've had microwave
curry three days in a row.

00:05:47.305 --> 00:05:48.515 position:50% align:center
Oh, hey!

00:05:48.556 --> 00:05:50.850 position:50% align:center
There's no school tomorrow,
if memory serves.

00:05:50.892 --> 00:05:52.769 position:50% align:center
Is your friend coming?

00:05:52.811 --> 00:05:54.312 position:50% align:center
Um, probably.

00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:56.356 position:50% align:center
[YURIKO inhales]
You think so?

00:05:56.398 --> 00:05:59.943 position:50% align:center
Oh! That's great!
I'm really excited now!

00:05:59.984 --> 00:06:00.985 position:50% align:center
It's not like he's
not coming over here

00:06:01.027 --> 00:06:03.405 position:50% align:center
to hang out with you, y'know.

00:06:03.446 --> 00:06:04.572 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:04.614 --> 00:06:06.783 position:50% align:center
[HORI] Wait! There's a good
chance he'll tell Mom his name!

00:06:06.825 --> 00:06:08.159 position:50% align:center
Got 'im!

00:06:08.493 --> 00:06:11.329 position:50% align:center
[door bell rings]

00:06:13.123 --> 00:06:15.959 position:50% align:center
You're finally here!
So nice to meet you.

00:06:16.001 --> 00:06:18.795 position:50% align:center
Don't be shy, please! Come in!

00:06:18.837 --> 00:06:21.381 position:50% align:center
Um, thank you.

00:06:21.423 --> 00:06:24.134 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA]
Wow. This must be Hori's mom!

00:06:24.175 --> 00:06:25.719 position:50% align:center
What a surprise.

00:06:25.760 --> 00:06:27.887 position:50% align:center
Uh. I brought some sweets.

00:06:27.929 --> 00:06:30.306 position:50% align:center
You did? So thoughtful!

00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:33.435 position:50% align:center
Sorry, but Kyoko isn't here.

00:06:33.476 --> 00:06:36.187 position:50% align:center
She's out and about
running some errands right now.

00:06:36.229 --> 00:06:38.940 position:50% align:center
She's told me so much
about you, though.

00:06:38.982 --> 00:06:40.650 position:50% align:center
--[SOTA] Hi, Mom!
--Ah!

00:06:40.692 --> 00:06:42.193 position:50% align:center
He's home late today.

00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:44.779 position:50% align:center
Hey! How you been, Bro?

00:06:44.821 --> 00:06:46.031 position:50% align:center
I see.

00:06:46.072 --> 00:06:48.491 position:50% align:center
That name really suits you!

00:06:48.533 --> 00:06:50.035 position:50% align:center
I would love to stay and chat.

00:06:50.076 --> 00:06:53.288 position:50% align:center
Honest. But, I sadly have
to get back to work.

00:06:53.329 --> 00:06:54.456 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA]
That's okay.

00:06:54.497 --> 00:06:56.124 position:50% align:center
I'll be heading out soon, too.

00:06:56.166 --> 00:06:57.542 position:50% align:center
[SOTA]
You're leaving already?

00:06:57.584 --> 00:06:59.544 position:50% align:center
But you just got here!

00:06:59.586 --> 00:07:01.046 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA chuckles]
Yeah.

00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:05.467 position:50% align:center
I appreciate you
helping out when you can.

00:07:05.508 --> 00:07:07.135 position:50% align:center
Well, sure.

00:07:07.177 --> 00:07:09.554 position:50% align:center
Huh? Where'd Mom go?

00:07:09.596 --> 00:07:13.350 position:50% align:center
Where else? She's at work.

00:07:13.391 --> 00:07:15.060 position:50% align:center
So, which one you wanna eat?

00:07:15.101 --> 00:07:16.144 position:50% align:center
Strawberry, please!

00:07:16.186 --> 00:07:17.312 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
That witch of a woman!

00:07:17.354 --> 00:07:19.314 position:50% align:center
She wanted her stupid
one-on-one time with him,

00:07:19.356 --> 00:07:21.066 position:50% align:center
so she sent me on errands!

00:07:21.107 --> 00:07:23.318 position:50% align:center
Man, the last time someone
called me my first name,

00:07:23.360 --> 00:07:24.861 position:50% align:center
I was in the sixth grade.

00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:27.113 position:50% align:center
It felt kinda weird.

00:07:27.155 --> 00:07:28.990 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
Wait. What?

00:07:29.032 --> 00:07:30.241 position:50% align:center
Talking about your mom.

00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:31.368 position:50% align:center
She used my first name.

00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:32.535 position:50% align:center
That's not what I meant!

00:07:32.577 --> 00:07:34.621 position:50% align:center
Do you mean how she used it?

00:07:34.662 --> 00:07:36.414 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh, uh-huh, uh-huh.

00:07:36.456 --> 00:07:37.749 position:50% align:center
Just as a greeting.

00:07:37.791 --> 00:07:40.835 position:50% align:center
She didn't use it
that much. But still...

00:07:40.877 --> 00:07:42.587 position:50% align:center
[HORI] Have the two of us
ever had a conversation

00:07:42.629 --> 00:07:44.756 position:50% align:center
where we were
both on the same page?

00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:46.508 position:50% align:center
Come on!

00:07:46.549 --> 00:07:48.760 position:50% align:center
That's not what I meant either!

00:07:48.802 --> 00:07:52.222 position:50% align:center
You know, recently, you've
been acting really strange.

00:07:52.263 --> 00:07:54.140 position:50% align:center
Me? What? No way!

00:07:54.182 --> 00:07:57.602 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA] Well, watching guys
change clothes is pretty weird.

00:07:57.644 --> 00:07:59.646 position:50% align:center
But, I had a reason for that.

00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:03.024 position:50% align:center
Hold on. Hori.

00:08:03.066 --> 00:08:04.401 position:50% align:center
Do you have a crush?

00:08:08.655 --> 00:08:10.240 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
No.

00:08:13.076 --> 00:08:14.452 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:17.080 position:50% align:center
Wait, my name?

00:08:17.122 --> 00:08:19.332 position:50% align:center
That's what you've been
so worried about?

00:08:19.374 --> 00:08:21.668 position:50% align:center
All because of a stupid name.

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:22.752 position:50% align:center
You are something else!

00:08:22.794 --> 00:08:24.713 position:50% align:center
That's one of the
lamest things I've ever heard!

00:08:24.754 --> 00:08:26.756 position:50% align:center
Excuse me for not
knowing how to ask you!

00:08:26.798 --> 00:08:29.217 position:50% align:center
I'm stealing
your pen real quick.

00:08:29.259 --> 00:08:29.759 position:50% align:center
Gimme a sec.

00:08:29.801 --> 00:08:31.511 position:50% align:center
[SOTA]
And lame-o was her name-oh!

00:08:31.553 --> 00:08:32.804 position:50% align:center
Sis! That hurts!

00:08:32.846 --> 00:08:34.931 position:50% align:center
Stop! Cut it out! Please!

00:08:38.727 --> 00:08:41.396 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
Izumi Miyamura.

00:08:41.438 --> 00:08:44.024 position:50% align:center
Ah! Forgot! Pronunciation.

00:08:44.065 --> 00:08:44.441 position:50% align:center
Give it back.

00:08:44.482 --> 00:08:45.650 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
I can pronounce it!

00:08:45.692 --> 00:08:49.571 position:50% align:center
Well, I'll go ahead
and hang on to this note.

00:08:49.612 --> 00:08:51.698 position:50% align:center
Just in case I forget it again.

00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:52.866 position:50% align:center
Aw, that sucks.

00:08:52.907 --> 00:08:54.325 position:50% align:center
Is my name really
that forgettable?

00:08:54.367 --> 00:08:56.494 position:50% align:center
No! I said just in case!

00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:59.164 position:50% align:center
You'll remember it
easier if you say it!

00:09:00.582 --> 00:09:02.751 position:50% align:center
Ee... Izumi.

00:09:02.792 --> 00:09:06.004 position:50% align:center
Right. There ya go.

00:09:10.759 --> 00:09:12.469 position:50% align:center
[HORI]
That felt super awkward.

00:09:12.510 --> 00:09:14.512 position:50% align:center
I'll just keep
calling you Miyamura!

00:09:14.554 --> 00:09:17.307 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA]
Jeez! What was that for, Hori?

00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:18.683 position:50% align:center
Wait, hold the phone!

00:09:18.725 --> 00:09:21.436 position:50% align:center
You're as clueless about my
first name as I was about yours!

00:09:21.478 --> 00:09:23.772 position:50% align:center
No. It's Kyoko?

00:09:26.316 --> 00:09:28.568 position:50% align:center
[HORI] The hole I'm digging
keeps getting deeper!

00:09:28.610 --> 00:09:31.404 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA] Hori says
the dumbest things sometimes.

00:09:31.446 --> 00:09:34.366 position:50% align:center
Ugh! What are you waiting for,
go ahead and laugh!

00:09:34.407 --> 00:09:36.618 position:50% align:center
[MIYAMURA] I'm good.
You'll just get mad if I laugh.

00:09:36.659 --> 00:09:38.411 position:50% align:center
You're damn right I will!

00:09:39.662 --> 00:09:41.164 position:50% align:center
You don't play fair!

00:09:47.796 --> 00:09:49.464 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry. Really.

00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:51.925 position:50% align:center
I can only imagine
how busy you are.

00:09:51.966 --> 00:09:53.301 position:50% align:center
It's totally cool!

00:09:53.343 --> 00:09:55.553 position:50% align:center
I'd do anything
for you, Sengoku.

00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:58.264 position:50% align:center
Thanks. You're a true lifesaver.

00:09:59.140 --> 00:10:01.726 position:50% align:center
Sakura. I trust
you'll handle these.

00:10:01.768 --> 00:10:03.436 position:50% align:center
Of course.

00:10:03.478 --> 00:10:04.938 position:50% align:center
It's amazing how
much smoother things go

00:10:04.979 --> 00:10:06.940 position:50% align:center
when you've got
capable people on the job.

00:10:06.981 --> 00:10:08.817 position:50% align:center
Huh. Yeah. I guess so.

00:10:08.858 --> 00:10:10.443 position:50% align:center
Which is why, if you don't mind.

00:10:10.485 --> 00:10:13.905 position:50% align:center
I, uh, I have another favor
I'd like to ask of you.

00:10:13.947 --> 00:10:14.989 position:50% align:center
What?

00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:17.158 position:50% align:center
Please? I know
it's inconvenient.

00:10:17.200 --> 00:10:18.034 position:50% align:center
But we're only asking

00:10:18.076 --> 00:10:20.704 position:50% align:center
because the student council
has so much to do!

00:10:20.745 --> 00:10:22.580 position:50% align:center
You're good.

00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:23.873 position:50% align:center
I know how it can be, so, yeah!

00:10:23.915 --> 00:10:25.333 position:50% align:center
No worries.

00:10:28.962 --> 00:10:31.631 position:50% align:center
Your eyes! Girl!

00:10:31.673 --> 00:10:33.466 position:50% align:center
Are they bad?

00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:37.303 position:50% align:center
This what the student council
dumped off on you?

00:10:37.345 --> 00:10:39.014 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:10:39.055 --> 00:10:40.765 position:50% align:center
[YOSHIKAWA] Why are
you stuck doing their work?

00:10:40.807 --> 00:10:42.100 position:50% align:center
You're not one of them.

00:10:42.142 --> 00:10:43.351 position:50% align:center
They have a lot of new members,

00:10:43.393 --> 00:10:45.937 position:50% align:center
so they're having a hard time
getting things done.

00:10:45.979 --> 00:10:47.731 position:50% align:center
[YOSHIKAWA]
Simple as that, huh?

00:10:47.772 --> 00:10:48.815 position:50% align:center
It just feels kinda messed up

00:10:48.857 --> 00:10:50.942 position:50% align:center
that they have you
do such important stuff.

00:10:50.984 --> 00:10:53.361 position:50% align:center
It's like they're using you
and you don't even care.

00:10:53.403 --> 00:10:54.654 position:50% align:center
